## How to Install broot
1- Download the broot binary for Raspberry Pi.

curl -o broot -L https://dystroy.org/broot/download/armv7-unknown-linux-gnueabihf/broot

2- Move the broot binary to the /usr/local/bin directory, and give the file execute permission:

 sudo mv broot /usr/local/bin
 sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/broot

3- Run broot with the following command:

broot

4- You are prompted to install the broot shell function. Choose Yes (Y) to continue.

5- Restart your shell session by exiting and logging back in, or source your ~/.bashrc file:
source ~/.bashrc

6-Verify the broot installation.
broot --version

7- You should get something like:
broot 1.13.3
